							</div>
			<div class="col">
				
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p><strong>This experiment was implemented to collect infrared images&nbsp;of the coal and gangue samples at the temperature of 323.15 K.&nbsp;Additionally, it showed that distinguishing between coal and&nbsp;gangue samples is feasible, although the area, thickness, and&nbsp;surface conditions were changed at a constant temperature&nbsp;during the process of capturing the infrared images. The coal and gangue were randomly collected from the same&nbsp;mine. The random samples had different weights, shapes, areas,&nbsp;thicknesses, and surface conations.&nbsp;</strong></p></div>
      
